events.name: Orlando Magic at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — R.J. Barrett scored 22 points and had 10 rebounds, and Julius Randle added 21 points and 17 rebounds to lead the New York Knicks to a 91-84 win over the Orlando Magic on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks' Barrett, Randle double up Magic

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — LaMarcus Aldridge had 22 points, DeMar DeRozan had 20 points and 11 assists as the San Antonio Spurs defeated the Portland Trail Blazers 125-104 on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Aldridge, DeRozan lead Spurs over Trail Blazers 125-104

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 17 points and 10 assists and took a key charge late as the Memphis Grizzlies won their fifth straight, beating the Phoenix Suns 108-104 on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant has 17 points, 10 assists; Grizzlies top Suns 108-104

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant made the go-ahead 3-pointer with 36 seconds left, James Harden had 34 points and 12 assists, and the Brooklyn Nets edged the Milwaukee Bucks 125-123 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden, Durant star as Nets edge Bucks 125-123

headlines.description: — The Miami Heat eventually showed up to a game already behind schedule.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat rally from 19 down, top Pistons 113-107 to end slide

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 26 points, Kelly Oubre Jr. added 23 and the Golden State Warriors rallied from a 14-point, fourth-quarter deficit to defeat the Los Angeles Lakers 115-113 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors rally from 14 down in 4th, beat Lakers 115-113
